sections.History:
===Background===
The Arbor is known for producing the [[Food and Drink#Wines|finest wines]] in the [[Seven Kingdoms]]. Due to their island location, their merchant ships require great protection at sea, so the [[Redwyne Fleet]] is one of the three largest in the realm. The Redwynes enjoy a particularly close relationship with its overlord, House Tyrell.&lt;ref&gt;[http://viewers-guide.hbo.com/season3/#!/locations/the-arbor/ HBO viewers guide, season 3 guide to houses, House Tyrell entry]&lt;/ref&gt;

In the current generation, Lady [[Olenna Tyrell]] was herself born Olenna Redwyne, before she married Lord [[Luthor Tyrell]].

===[[Season 2]]===
House Redwyne follows their liege lords of House Tyrell in supporting [[Renly Baratheon]]'s claim to the [[Iron Throne]].&lt;ref&gt;Season 2 bluray: War of the Five Kings feature&lt;/ref&gt;

===[[Season 4]]===
The Redwyne sigil is present at the [[Purple Wedding|royal wedding]].&lt;ref&gt;The Lion and the Rose&lt;/ref&gt;
